explanation: [0-0] Below a grassy field are two underground rooms connected by a narrow passage. The left room stores corn and cheese, while the right room contains a bed. Both rooms have a yellow lamp, and the right room has a periscope above it. A tree stands on the grassland on the right side.

[0-6] A mouse appears in the frame, carrying a carrot. A man holding a pitchfork emerges to the mouse's left. The man wears a black T-shirt and gray shorts. The mouse jumps down the passage, and the man drops the pitchfork. Wooden planks on both sides of the rooms form a bridge. The mouse falls onto the bridge, reaches the left room, and drops the carrot. It then runs to the right room. The planks close off the entrance to the left room, trapping the mouse inside the right room. Standing on the planks, the mouse observes the man through the periscope. After the man departs, the entrance to the right room is also closed.
